        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-12T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-13T11:00:00+07:00">November 13, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1969. Undated telegram from Stevens,<note n="19" xml:id="d466fn19">Harry E.
                        Stevens, Second Secretary of Embassy in China.</note> Peiping, received
                    today states that available local information indicates Communists have
                    intensified operations in Shansi and Suiyuan; Communists are converging from
                    several directions on Tatung, Kueisui is still under intensive infantry attacks;
                    Communist forces now encircling Kueisui comprising 36 regiments under Ho Lung
                    are reported to have stated recently that Communist forces will start large
                    scale civil war if Central Government refuses to accept proposed Communist
                    settlement of present crises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
